        "content": "<p>Is there an existing package/function for formatting a string into a valid url?<br>\nFor instance, replacing spaces with <code>%20</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Julia\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">str</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s\">\"https://julialang.zulipchat.com/word1 word2.com\"</span>\n<span class=\"s\">\"https://julialang.zulipchat.com/word1 word2.com\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">julia</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">url</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">replace</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s\">\" \"</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"s\">\"%20\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"s\">\"https://julialang.zulipchat.com/word1%20word2.com\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 266667264,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakir Luc Gagnon",
        "timestamp": 1641202805
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=HTTP.jl&amp;type=Repositories\">HTTP.jl</a> has this functionality in it's URI module</p>",
